\begin{enumerate}
\item
$tr(A)=\sum a_{ii}$
\item
$tr(A + B) = tr(A) + tr(B)$
\item 
$tr(cA) = ctr(A)$
\item
$tr(AB) = tr(BA)$
\item
Let u and v both be $m \times 1$ vectors. Then $tr(uv') = u'v = v'u$. 

[Example application: If we are given a square matrix A, then there doesn't exist  another square matrix X that satisfies the equation AX âˆ’ XA = I because the trace of the LHS is 0 and the trace of the RHS is 1.]
